<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1849-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1849-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Clayton</persName>,
                                    Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hall</persName>,
                                    district attorney</hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Confidential.—Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1849-09-06"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 6,
                                    1849</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">J. Prescott Hall</hi>,
                                    Esq.,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States District Attorney, New
                                    York:</hi></p>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your attention is again called to your
                                instructions respecting the expedition against Cuba. Arrest any
                                vessel engaged in it. We learn here that they are about to sail.</p>
                            <p>Yours, respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>J. M. CLAYTON.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>